PROJECT CONTEXT

The frontend is a React application located in VMA-frontend.
The backend folder contains a Python script `voice_live_quickstart.py`.

The file `voice_live_quickstart.py` already works and is responsible for connecting to the Azure Voice Live API and enabling voice-to-voice conversation with the AI agent.

The `.env` file in the backend folder already contains all required Azure credentials and environment variables.

Currently the backend script works when run manually, but it is NOT exposed as an HTTP API that the React frontend can call.

Your job is to create a small FastAPI backend wrapper around this script so the React frontend can trigger the voice interaction.

IMPORTANT CONSTRAINTS

Do NOT modify the core Azure voice logic inside `voice_live_quickstart.py`.

Do NOT implement:
- authentication
- databases
- reports
- deal clinic logic
- analytics
- session history storage

This backend should ONLY act as a thin API layer that triggers the existing voice agent.

The goal is simply to allow the React frontend to:

1) Start a conversation with the AI voice agent
2) End the conversation


BACKEND REQUIREMENTS

Create a FastAPI backend inside the `backend` folder.

Add a new file:

backend/main.py

This file should expose two API endpoints:


1) START CONVERSATION

POST /start-conversation

This endpoint should start the voice interaction by calling the logic inside `voice_live_quickstart.py`.

This endpoint will be called when the user clicks the **"Talk to Customer"** button in the React UI.

The backend should start the voice session asynchronously so the server does not block.


2) END CONVERSATION

POST /end-conversation

This endpoint should gracefully stop the running voice session.


SERVER REQUIREMENTS

Use FastAPI + Uvicorn.

Add CORS middleware so that the React frontend running on localhost can call the backend.

Allow all origins for now (development mode).


